            "description": "The Extended Reality & Game Development Lab is a specialized facility designed for hands-on learning and research in Virtual Reality (VR), Augmented Reality (AR), and Mixed Reality (MR). The lab is equipped with advanced XR devices such as Microsoft HoloLens and Meta VR headsets, high-performance systems, and development tools used for creating immersive applications and games.This lab enables students to work on real-time game development, 3D visualization, interactive simulations, and virtual walkthroughs. It supports learning in areas like Unity/Unreal game engines, XR application development, human–computer interaction, and immersive technology research. The lab plays a key role in enhancing practical skills, innovation, and industry-ready experience in extended reality and game development domains."
